{
  "stem": "25598.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And only until I finished university and started looking around at the reality of life did I realize that communism ain't what it-- what it says in books it is.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And then I had a tremendous depression, tremendous depression, because I had invested myself completely, emotionally, into this idea.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And the fact that I suddenly realized that it's not what I thought it was was a terrible blow-- terrible blow.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Before that, mind you, my parents wanted to leave.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "My-- my parents woke up earlier.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "My-- my father was never a communist.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "My mother woke up before me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And they wanted to leave to Israel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "But there was no way I would leave.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And I was the only child, so of course they didn't leave, which is a great source of sadness for me, because had they left to Israel in the late '40s rather than at the early '60s, they might have still made a life for themselves in Israel and learned the language and-- and adapted.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And in the late '60s they were both old and-- and they just couldn't make it there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In the meantime, my Uncle Armin and Aunt Mila had ran away to Belgium, where they lived for several years, where their two children were born, Diana and Murray.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And from there, they immigrated to Canada.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And they brought us out from Israel to Canada.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "They used to live in Montreal.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1963.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were for two years in Israel, from '61 to '63.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I had all kinds of interesting jobs in Israel, and-- and really, Israel, for me, was the best thing.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, I loved it, and I loved life there.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
